Project Name

SP Chains – B2B Silver Trading Application

Project Overview

Build a B2B Silver Trading Web Application for SP Chains that allows registered dealers to browse silver products, view live MCX-based pricing, calculate weight and amount, place orders, apply coupons, select payment modes, and submit reviews.
The system must include an Admin Panel and integrate with an ERP system via APIs.

Technology Stack (Strict)

Frontend: React (Web App)

Admin Panel: React

Backend: Python (FastAPI preferred)

Database: PostgreSQL

Auth: OTP + JWT

ERP Integration: REST APIs

Notifications: Firebase (Push) + Email

Hosting: Cloud/VPS (Docker ready)

User Roles

Dealer (User)

Admin

ERP (External System – API only)

Core Functional Modules
1. Dealer Registration & Approval

Dealer Flow

Register using:

Business Name

GST Number

PAN Number

Mobile Number

Validate inputs (format + uniqueness)

Send OTP for mobile verification

Submit registration request

Admin Flow

View pending dealer registrations

Approve / Reject dealer

Approved dealers can login

2. Authentication

Mobile number + OTP login

JWT-based authentication

Role-based access control

Session expiry handling

3. Product Catalogue (ERP Driven)

Fetch product list from ERP

Product fields:

Product ID

Name

Category

Available Sizes

Base Weight

Stock Quantity

Making Charges

Filters:

Category

Size

Stock availability

4. Pricing Engine

Fetch MCX Silver Rate from ERP

Apply pricing logic:

Net Rate = MCX + Premium

Wholesale Rate = Net Rate

Retail Rate = Wholesale + 1%

Pricing must be real-time & accurate

Admin can configure premium %

5. Checkout – Weight & Amount Calculation

Dealer selects:

Product

Size

Quantity

System calculates:

Gross Weight

Pure Weight

Wastage

Making Charges

Final Amount Formula:

Final Amount = (Pure Weight × Rate) + Making Charges


Display calculation breakdown clearly

6. Payment Mode & Dealer Credit

Payment modes:

Online

Dealer Credit

Dealer credit flow:

Validate credit availability via ERP

Approve or reject credit

Save payment status with order

7. Coupon Engine

Apply coupon code

Validate coupon rules:

Minimum quantity

Payment mode

Expiry date

Accept or reject coupon

Apply discount if valid

8. Order Management

Confirm order from dealer

Save order in backend

Lock stock in ERP

Order statuses:

Placed

Approved

Rejected

Completed

Display order history to dealer

9. Notifications System

Admin can create notifications:

Offers

Alerts

GST updates

Notification delivery:

Push notifications

Email

In-app alerts

10. Review & Rating System

Dealer can submit:

Rating (1–5)

Review text

Save review to ERP

Update product rating

Admin Panel Features

Dealer approval management

Product view (read-only from ERP)

Pricing premium configuration

Coupon creation & rules

Notification publishing

Order monitoring dashboard

Database Design (High Level)
Tables

users

dealer_profiles

otp_logs

products (cached from ERP)

orders

order_items

payments

coupons

notifications

reviews

API Requirements

REST APIs only

Secure with JWT

ERP API wrapper layer

Proper error handling

Logging for:

Pricing

Orders

Payments

Non-Functional Requirements

High accuracy for pricing & weight

ERP failure handling

Secure authentication

Scalable architecture

Clean React UI (B2B focused)